In `platform/mcp-server/src/mcp-setup.ts` around line 338, the tabId property is injected as:
```typescript
properties.tabId = {
  type: 'integer',
  description: '...',
};
```

Change to:
```typescript
properties.tabId = {
  type: 'integer',
  minimum: 1,
  description: '...',
};
```

This only affects plugin tools (the injection loop at line 332-349). Browser tools that accept their own tabId parameter (like browser_execute_script, browser_click_element, etc.) define their schemas separately via Zod in `platform/mcp-server/src/browser-tools/`. Check if any browser tool schemas define a `tabId` parameter with z.number() and add .min(1) if so — search for `tabId` in `platform/mcp-server/src/browser-tools/` to find them.

Note: For plugin tools, tabId is extracted BEFORE Ajv validation (mcp-tool-dispatch.ts line 323), so the minimum:1 constraint on the schema is informational for MCP clients — the server strips tabId before validation. But it still helps MCP clients that validate locally. For browser tools, tabId goes through Ajv directly, so minimum:1 would reject invalid values with a clear error.
